.TH syscall 2
.SH NAME
\*Lsyscall\*O \- indirect system call
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*Lsyscall(\*Vnumber\*O, \*Varg\*L, \*V...\*L)\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "syscall system call"
.iX "system call" "performing indirect"
The \*Lsyscall\*O system call performs the system call whose assembly language
interface has the specified \*Vnumber\*O, register arguments
\*Lr0\*O and \*Lr1\*O, and further arguments \*Varg\*O.
.PP
The \*Lr0\*O value of the system call is returned.
.SH RESTRICTIONS
.PP
There is no way to simulate system calls such as \*Lpipe\*O,
which return values in register \*Lr1\*O.
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
.PP
When the C-bit is set, \*Lsyscall\*O returns \-1 and sets the
external variable \*Lerrno\*O.
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.PP
Functions: \*Lerrno\*O(2), \*Lpipe\*O(2)
